Content Modification Time; Name: OUT-OF~1.DOC Origin: Out-of\u2011date-GmbH secrects.lnk` | Creation/modification of the shortcut that points to the secret file. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f17:12:40 | `LNK; Creation Time; C:\\Documents and Settings\\Administrator\\Desktop\\Out-of\u2011date\u2011GmbH secrects.docx` | The shortcut was created on the Desktop \u2013 the user was preparing to access the file. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f17:14:51 | `LOG; Last Time Executed; WORDPAD.EXE was run 1 time(s)` | WordPad was used to open the .docx file, indicating the file was actually viewed. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f17:14:16 | `REG; Content Modification Time; \u2026\\USBSTOR.SYS` (and related USB registry keys) | A USB mass\u2011storage device was plugged in at 17:14:16 \u2013 the likely medium for exfiltration. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f17:15:13 | `FILE; crtime; \u2026/RECYCLER/S-1-5-21-\u2026/desktop.ini` (and similar Recycle Bin timestamps) | The original file was deleted and moved to the Recycle Bin, a common cover\u2011up step. |\n\nThe chain \u2013 shortcut creation \u2192 file opening \u2192 USB plug\u2011in \u2192 deletion \u2013 is exactly what one would expect if an employee copied the recipe file to a USB drive and then erased it from the mainframe.\n\n**Is the Internet actually deactivated?**  \n**No** \u2013 The presence of many `WEBHIST` events that reference external host names proves that the machine was able to reach the Internet on 19\u202fApril\u202f2017:\n\n| Timestamp | Event | Why it matters |\n|-----------|-------|----------------|\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f01:36:14 | `WEBHIST; Expiration Time; http://images.sport1.de/\u2026` | External URL accessed. |\n| \u2026 | `WEBHIST; Expiration Time; http://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/\u2026` | External CDN accessed. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f09:03:14 | `WEBHIST; Expiration Time; http://assets.sport1.de/\u2026` | More external resources loaded. |\n| 2017\u201104\u201119\u202f16:12:22 | `WEBHIST; Expiration Time; Cookie:administrator@www.sport1.de/` | A cookie for an external domain was set \u2013 the browser was communicating with an external server. |\n| \u2026 | `WEBHIST; Last Visited Time; \u2026:2017041920170420: Administrator@file:///C:/\u2026` | Local file accesses are logged as web history, but the preceding external entries still demonstrate Internet traffic. |\n\nIf the mainframe had truly been isolated from the Internet, none of these external\u2011domain web\u2011history entries (which are normally generated only when a browser actually fetches the resource) would appear. Therefore the assumption that the Internet was deactivated is contradicted by the evidence.\n\n**Bottom line**\n\n- **Yes** \u2013 An employee accessed, copied to a USB drive, and deleted the secret recipe document.  \n- **No** \u2013 The system was still connected to the Internet, as shown by the numerous external web\u2011history events.<|return|>",
